\cb7 The\'a0
\f12\b where
\f11\b0 \'a0layer (Z, G, GK, H) defines the map: what the network looks like, which segments exist, which paths an attacker could walk, and which nodes are critical enough to anchor coverage math to.\cb1 \
\cb7 The\'a0
\f12\b score
\f11\b0 \'a0layer (
\f4 \uc0\u8900 
\f11 , \uc0\u961 , iv, \u963 , w) defines how the solver evaluates a plan: which techniques does each type detect, how likely is each path, how valuable is each interception, how sensitive is each honeypot, and what's the weight hierarchy that encodes prevention-over-forensics.\cb1 \
