\f16\b0 \cf0 q
\f5 \uc0\u8346 
\f16  
\f4 \uc0\u8712 
\f16  [0,1] is the probability weight the solver assigns to each persona p when calculating detection credit. All priors must sum to 1 across all personas in P. It is updated by Algorithm 1 whenever threat intelligence changes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f17\b \cf0 What q
\f5\b0 \uc0\u8346 
\f17\b  means in the credit formula:
\f16\b0 \
Every soft-clause credit is multiplied by q
\f5 \uc0\u8346 
\f16 . A Finance_DB honeypot deployment that would normally earn W = 1.995 credit units earns 1.995 \'d7 q_\{Finance_DB\} instead. If q_\{Finance_DB\} = 0.45, the deployment earns 1.995 \'d7 0.45 = 0.898. If q_\{Finance_DB\} = 0.10, the same deployment earns only 1.995 \'d7 0.10 = 0.200.\

