\f13 \uc0\u7496 
\f16 (i,z,t) = \uc0\u964 
\f13 \uc0\u7496 
\f20 \uc0\u8304 
\f16  \'d7 (1 \uc0\u8722  \u961 \u960 (t) / \u961 
\f5 \cf14 \uc0\u8344 \u8336 
\f13 \cf14 \uc0\u739 
\f16 )\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f17\b \cf0 What goes wrong without \uc0\u961 
\f5\b0 \uc0\u8344 \u8336 
\f6\b \uc0\u739 
\f17 :
\f16\b0 \
If \uc0\u961 \u960  could equal 1.0 in the formula and \u961 
\f5 \uc0\u8344 \u8336 
\f13 \uc0\u739 
\f16  = 1.0:\
