\cf0 Catching at hop 1 prevents all subsequent damage. Catching at hop 3 only records what has already happened. The path ordering is what gives the formulation its prevention-versus-forensics distinction. Without ordered paths, every detection event would look the same regardless of when in the intrusion it occurred.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f17\b \cf0 Where G comes from in practice:
\f16\b0 \
First National Financial already runs RedSeal Network Security Manager, which continuously maps the network topology and generates attack path reports. Every week the dashboard shows the ten most probable attacker routes based on current firewall rules and known vulnerabilities. The security team exports these in STIX format. Algorithm 1 ingests this feed and updates \uc0\u961  values when new threat intelligence arrives.\
